title: For Sale:  Smith and Wesson 669 Custom
postcontent: I have a lightly customized second generation Smith and Wesson 9mm for sale.  It is a Model 669, double stack 9mm pistol.  The pistol was completely disassembled in 2011: springs, trigger, and rear sight block were replaced, and the aluminum frame was professionally anondized a deep navy blue color.  It was reassembled by Lockburner Firearms in Colorado Springs.  The barrel and all fire control parts were cerakoted black, while the slide recieved a dark graphite cerakote from Pittsburgh Cerakote company last year.  All engravings are still clearly legible (it's my picture taking that sucks). I originally bought this gun because of my fascination with the early Paris ASP and Devel modifications to first generation S&W automatics, and their influence on early CCW pistols. The 669 incorporates some of the advancements of the ASP and Devel customs: shortened grip and slide, smoothed surfaces and aggressive trigger hook.  It is a DA/SA, double stack, 9mm with 13 round capacity and slide mounted safety/decocker.  The 669 was originally designed as a concealed carry weapon for the law enforcement market during the early 1980s.  While CCW has come a long way since then, this pistol remains a reliable carry piece and unique throwback for Smith and Wesson collectors.  Comes with 3 magazines, (2 finger extension and 1 flush fit).  Since rebuilding, I have put very few rounds through it to test function, and it has been a safequeen since.  Price is $475, which is well below what I have into the gun. Transfer will have to go through an FFL somewhere between SW Pittsburgh and Washington, choice is up to you.  Thanks!The only trade I am interested in is a vz61 Skorpion in .32 ACP with wood grips (Czechpoint preferred).

title: For Sale:  Dan Wesson revolver
postcontent: This is the adulated Dan Wesson .357 revolver. It touts an interchangeable barrel system which allows you to precisely set the cylinder gap, and has the revolver signature of craftsmanship, the recessed cylinder. These revolvers were a departure from S&W's regular production guns by the grandson of its founder. Same great reliability, but these guns had features like interchangeable front sights, solid wood grips, a wide choice of barrels that the user could exchange, and a much improved double/single action trigger pull. The .357 magnum is arguably the best personal defense caliber ever developed, and this gun carries 6 in a safe compact package that easily converts to a long range target pistol. This particular offering has the 2 1/2" and 8" barrels, and the necessary tools for making the switch. I'd be happy to show you how to change them over, it takes about a minute. I have had this gun for about 5 years, but I've only fired a few cylinders of .38's through it. Wonderful, dependable example of what many believe to be one of the best revolvers ever made in America. The previous owner was a private detective, so both barrels show some holster wear, and the finish is intact with light scratches from the same. I'm listing it with both barrels and tools for $600, but I'd sell the gun and either barrel for $500. Please feel free to contact me if you have questions, and I'll answer them as best I can. Additional pictures are available if needed, armslist will only allow me to post one. Thanks for looking!
